# Cursor AI Backend Configuration — MiniMax-M2.7
# Reference: https://platform.minimax.io/docs/llms.txt (Cursor integration guide)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
## CONTEXT BUDGET RULE
Every task that requires reading/modifying more than 2 files MUST
output a subagent manifest before writing any code.
Do not attempt to handle multi-file tasks in the main agent.


## ⚠️ PREREQUISITE: Cursor Pro subscription required
Without Pro, configuring MiniMax-M2.7 results in:
"The model MiniMax-M2.7 does not work with your current plan or api key"

## ⚠️ KNOWN ISSUE: "Override OpenAI Base URL" is GLOBAL
Once enabled, it applies to ALL API keys (Anthropic, GPT, etc.).
If Claude/GPT stop working after enabling, disable the override when not using MiniMax.
Cursor does not yet support per-model base URLs.
→ https://forum.cursor.com/t/custom-base-urls-for-each-custom-model/147219

## SETUP STEPS (follow in order)

### Step 1: Clear conflicting OpenAI env vars
Before configuring, unset any existing OpenAI vars:
- `OPENAI_API_KEY`
- `OPENAI_BASE_URL`

### Step 2: Configure API Key in Cursor Settings
1. Open Cursor → Settings → Models (left sidebar)
2. Expand "API Keys" section
3. Enable "Override OpenAI Base URL"
4. Base URL: `https://api.minimax.io/v1` (international) or `https://api.minimaxi.com/v1` (China)
5. Paste API key from https://platform.minimax.io/user-center/payment/token-plan
6. Click the button right of the API Key field to verify
7. Click "Enable OpenAI API Key" in the popup

### Step 3: Add Custom Model
1. In the Models section, click "View All Models"
2. Click "Add Custom Model"
3. Enter exactly: `MiniMax-M2.7` (capital M, lowercase i, hyphen — exact spelling)
4. Click "Add"

### Step 4: Enable and Select
1. Enable the newly added "MiniMax-M2.7" model (toggle)
2. Select "MiniMax-M2.7" in the chat panel dropdown

## NOTE: Tab Autocomplete
Tab (Cursor Pro feature) uses Cursor's own model — NOT your custom MiniMax key.
Custom models only work in: Chat / Composer / Edit modes.

## APPLICATION CODE vs CURSOR BACKEND
Your cekwajar.id application code uses MiniMax via OpenAI SDK:
  baseURL: https://api.minimax.io/v1
  (configured in src/lib/agents/ and cekwajar.mdc)
This is SEPARATE from Cursor's backend model above.